<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8737> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8737" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 751, footnote 354" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 80?, Procos. 79? See MRR 2.79, 84, 85, note 4. His praetorship should almost certainly be redated to 81 and his proconsulate in Hisp. Cit. to 80 (Salt. Hist 1.111M), with his death in battle against Hirtuleius, Sertorius' quaestor (Plut. Sert. 12.4, and other sources listed in MRR). On the verso of the Vienna fragment of Sallust's Histories, see Bischoff-Bloch, WS, n.s. 13, 1979, 116-129. Note that several of the too many names listed for the praetors of 81 (MRR 2.76) have been placed only at the latest legal date. Some must have held the office in previous years.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4271> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4271" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Nearer Spain (Sall. Hist. 1.111M; Plut. Sert. 12.8; of. Liv. Per. 90, Legatus). Defeated and killed in battle on the Anas by Hirtuleius, Quaestor of Sertorius (Sall. Hist. 1.111M; Liv. Per. 90; Frontin. Str. 4.5.19; Plut. Sert. 12.3-4; Flor. 2.10.7; Eutrop. 6.1.2; Oros. 5.23.3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4270> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4270" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "4 Domitius' praenomen is given as M. in Livy and L. in Eutropius. The cognomen Calvinus is an emendation for the readings # in Plutarch. He is termed Legatus in Florus and the Periochae of Livy, and Praetor in Eutropius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4232> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4232" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Eutrop. 6.1.2, praetor. See 79, Promagistrates." .
